<div id="banner">
	<h1>Microsoft Software So Insecure It Could Cost Lives</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Microsoft VP Jim Allchin<a href="http://www.eweek.com/print_article/0,3668,a=26875,00.asp">has testified that Microsoft code is so insecure it cannot be disclosed</a>. As ESR points out, either a) Microsoft is lying or b) Microsoft has decided that the loss of American lives isn&#8217;t worth enough to fix the code.<br />
</p>

<p class="posted">posted May 23, 2002 06:49 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000285" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

